title: Fixed a NPE in RingtonePreference summary binding
Snooze stopped working
body:
Recently (a week?) Snooze/set later time stopped working for me. I set a new time for a later alarm, but the alarm does not sound. 

OS: LineageOS 14.1-20180801-NIGHTLY-athene on Moto G4.

title: Vulnerability in 2.9.01 as per F-Droid
body:
Privet Yura,
I have been using your great app as a main alarmclock for many years. Unfortunately, F-Droid didn't update the app since 2.9.01. And now F-Droid even recommends to uninstall the app due to known vulnerabilities and disabled algorithm. Notsure why they did not uodate their build to the latest version. Do you have any idea on the issue?
As for now, I'm still using airgapped ancient lenovo device with 4.2.1 Android mainly because of your app. At the same time my main phone is latest pixel xl with android 8, but due to the F-Droid warning I'm not risking to install your app.
It would be really beneficial if you could upload .apk builds here as well.
Thank you for the app!

Refactored klaxon service for better testability
Added a few lines to coverage

title: Refactor time picker validation
label: [Label(name="Next")]
body: At the moment there is a huge if with no real code coverage. No good. Has to be refactored.

title: Get rid of the custom RingtonePreference
Can disable fade-in
body:
Patch for issue #226 
Doesn't totally disable fade-in, but allows setting it to 1 second, which should be close enough.
Also did a bit of cleanup by removing unnecessary translations of integers (which are the same no matter the language, obviously)

title: Optimistic time update in the list after picker
Add a Codacy badge to README.md
Removed save/restore instance state in time picker
Added a test for 24/12 hours mode
Added some long timeout options to adb
Add option for having a custom snooze value
body: This change adds a "Custom" option to the snooze time selector, and a preference option to set a custom time in minutes for the snooze time, that will be activated when "Custom" is selected.

title: Dialog disappears on device rotation

1. Click on ...
2. Click on Settings
3. Click on Alarm Volume
4. Orientation Change

The dialog disappears unlike the dialogs associated with other preferences in the same list

title: [feature-request] How about an alternate TimePicker?
body: I (personally) would like to see an alternative Date- and/or TimePicker, like the following example: Source: https://github.com/rubenroy/Minimal-Todo What do you mean? I don't know what an effort that could be. I just saw the current picker (https://github.com/yuriykulikov/AlarmClock/blob/develop/src/main/java/com/better/alarm/presenter/TimePickerDialogFragment.java) and the other picker (https://github.com/rubenroy/Minimal-Todo/blob/master/app/src/main/java/com/example/avjindersinghsekhon/minimaltodo/AddToDoActivity.java) which is open source, too; and would like to ask that question to you and other people, here.

title: [bug?] Edit alarm doesn't work
body:
I'm on AlarmClock v2.9.01 on my Samsung i9100 @ AOSP 4.2.2.

After opening the app I saw two already existing alarms. I long pressed on one of them and selected 'Edit alarm', but nothing happens. The same on the other alarm and on self created alarms, too.
The other both points ('Turn alarm on/off' and 'Delete alarm') are working as expected.

Because there is the 'encircled triangle-sign' on the right side of each alarm, which let me edit the alarm(s), this is not a big deal. But I thought you should know that.

title: [feature-request] Off option for 'fade-in duration'
label: [Label(name="Next")]
body:
First of all thanks a lot for your enthusiasm and sharing such a neat and useful app to the community!

I'm on AlarmClock v2.9.01 on my Samsung i9100 @ AOSP 4.2.2 and wanted to disable the fade-in feature, but I can't find an option for that.

I thought it would be cool, if you could add an 'Off' option inside the Settings -> 'Fade-in duration' point, (as it's the case under the 'Pre-alarm duration' point, already).

Thank in advance for any help or support.

title: Where is the androidUtils module?
body: Where is the androidUtils module?

title: Failed to build with error ':androidUtils' could not be found in root project 'AlarmClock'
body:
Hello, 

First of all, thanks for the great app. I wanna build the app in the git repo. So I cloned the master, and load into Android Studio. 

However, when I build the project, I encountered the following error

`> Project with path ':androidUtils' could not be found in root project 'AlarmClock'.`

which comes from the definition

```
dependencies {
    compile project(':androidUtils')
    ...
```

Could you point me how to build the app? Thank you very much!

title: После окончания разговора бесконечно звучит мелодия будильника на одной громкости
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body:
Добрый день!
Спасибо за вашу программу - сегодня стал пользователем. И сегодня же обнаружил один неприятный глюк:
1. Стоит нарастающий звук 30 секунд.
2. Срабатывает будильник.
3. Отключаю будильник долгим нажатием на остановить.
4. Вроде все хорошо остановлен.
5. Мне звонят (когда я звоню все ок).
6. После окончания разговора бесконечно звучит мелодия будильника на одной громкости.
7. Киляние будильника в списке задач останавливает звук.

Эту последовательность я повторял несколько раз. Телефон Lenovo p780. Прошивка последняя официальная ...s123.
Будильник нравиться, отказываться не собираюсь. Готов быть бета тестором. Если вы не почините, то придется самому поразбираться в жаве (я на с++ программирую).

title: Snooze cannot be turned off
body:
There is no option "Off" in snooze time. There are users which do not like it. We should add an option "Off" and do not snooze in this case.

Proposed changes:
- add an option and "Off" to the list in arrays.xml and strings.xml . Integer value can be -1
- AlarmCore.java - in onSnooze() in FiredState in case value of setting is -1 should not do anything.

title: Consider moving action menu from settings to the main activity
Removed feature: Holding Snooze Button
body:
The following feature does not work anymore:
If I wake up because of the Alarm clock I usually grab my phone without looking at it, because my eyes are still closed. Then i put my finger on the middle of the screen to snooze  and hold it on the screen.Then i move the phone slowly  in front of my face with the eyes still closed and I'am nearly sleeping during this process. Then i  open my eyes only shortly to see if the big snooze area is enlighted or the small cancel area is enlighted. If the big area is enlighted i release my finger and i sleep until the next alarm. If the small area is enlighted i move my finger to the big area and then release it.
So I don't have to get awake and mistakes are unlikely.
With the app this feature doesn't work anymore because i can't hold my finger on the cancel area for long without activating the alarm cancelation.
And touching and holding on the snooze area does not work because of the snooze time selection. But this can be solved with an option to deactivate the snooze time selection in the preferences.
Hopefully this will help to improve the app.
My version is 2.5.07.
Thanks
Alex

title: skip next, e.g. when you have a long weekend allow skipping of the instance of a recurring alarm
label: [Label(name="Next")]
body: not a bug, a feature request. skip next, e.g. when you have a long weekend allow skipping of the next 1-n instances of a recurring alarm. means you don't have to worry about remembering to turn an alarm back on. it's the only feature missing :-)

title: системе оно значится как "Часы", хотя на ярлыке "Будильник"
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: в системе оно значится как "Часы", хотя на ярлыке "Будильник", из за такого несовпадения не сразу разобрался, но это мелочи

title: Most presenters do not require a service
body: Basically everything can be reduced to alarm service, klaxon and vibe, dB service and activities. Toast, notification and either presenters can be created in on create. There is nothing heavy there so we don,t care about on demand.

title: Sort alarms list
body: Is there a way to make the alarms show up in numerical order? Example 7:45 would come up before 8:00, but it seems to come up after it because of the order in which I created the alarms.

title: Der Wecker zeigt alle paar Minuten an, in wievielen Stunden und Sekunden er klingeln wird, daa würde ich gerne ausschalten.

title: GUI and sm sync are required for notifications and status bar
Snooze to time does not work in prealarm
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body:
Hint
Prealarmsnoozedstate.enter()

title: Settings as "dailogIfLarge" does not allow to use menu
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: Besides, causes crashes on some devices

title: Volume control is somewhat buggy
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: There is a spike on the default volume at the beginning

title: Alarm fade in should be smooth and configurable
body:
- Duration must be configurable in settings
- Fade in steps should be small

title: geht der Wecker trotz richtiger Differenznzeige nicht an
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body:
seit dem Update von Sony geht der Wecker trotz richtiger Differenznzeige nicht an. Erst wenn das Handy wieder in Gebrauch genommen wird wird der Wecker aktiviert und zeigt die tatsächliche Zeit als Weckzeit an. In den Einstellungen hat sich die Zeit aber nicht verändert. Auch eine Neuinstallation bringt keine Veränderung . wünsche trotzdem frohe Ostern

title: app start is not handled properly
body:
When app starts
- Alarms should submit their RTCs, without advancing the date
- If then refresh comes, do refresh
- If alarm is in the past
  - it should wait for a message.
  - This can be potentially dangerous. For example 2 alarms are scheduled for the same time, only one will get a message then?

title: Implement a host service and do all work therem
body: Use one receiver and one service to do the work. This service will be responsible for creating presenters and distributing events to them.

title: Use multiple select mode to access context menu
body: This closes #5

title: Updating the app crashes
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: DB issue

title: Alarm should be parcelable
body: related to #42

title: Refactor alarm alert to have only one alert
body: We should not use Theme.Holo.Wallpaper.NoTitleBar to remove KeyGuard. Instead, we should remove it ourselves. This will allow us to have only one AlarmAlert class and no tablet-specific layouts.

title: Fullscreen alrt on tablets looks awful
label: [Label(name="bug")]

title: AlarmCore should not handle DB and ContentValues
body:
- Active record container
- or
- saveing strategy

title: Replace checkboxes with switches
body: Checkboxes can be confused with group selection.

title: Merge JB
body: Merge JB source for translations

title: Catch exceptions and log them before showing the error dialog
Alert dialogs are dark
body: Shouldn't, they be light too?

title: More refactoring
body:
The model concept is not clear yet.

What should alarm do?
What should manager do?
- Tossing ID's around is not nice. Much nicer to toss alarm objects. If alarm is parcel able, there is almost no need for manager in presenters.
- How new alarms should be created?
- How go to bed alarms should be different?
- How much alarms should be aware of each other?
- How to handle persistence? It seems OK how it is handled now.

title: Vibration should be configurable
body: Currently always vibrates. Should be configurable per alarm and a default setting should be present.

title: React on set alarm system intent
Use light sensor
body: Use the light sensor to get screen darker in the bedroom

title: New timer picker is nice to have
Consider movind add button from he action bar back to the list
Go Tod bed button should be in time picker
Prealarm volume should be configurable
body: Settings entry is required

title: Alarms are not scheduled on boot
label: [Label(name="bug")]

title: Replace pre-alarm checkbox with time selector
body: As proposed by @sheremi , we have to replace a checkbox with radio popup. Value in settings can be used as a default value in this case.

title: Time zone change is not handled properly
label: [Label(name="bug")]

title: Pre alarm behaves strange
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body:
Observed:
- expired was still scheduled
- Snoozed notification does not disable the alarm

title: Snooze did not go
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: Snooze alarm did not go and there was no scheduled alarm on the lockscreen afterwards. Snooze notification was still present.

title: Replace notification with callback with a broadcastreceiver.
body: Notification with a callback does not look good, because changes to the GUI can be done from an Alarm receiver service. Ok, it is still on the same thread, but from design it is not nice.

title: Do not use dialog for time picker, use built-in layout
body: This saves two clicks. But we need enough space, so maybe this is only for tablets/phablets. Or use horizontal scrolling or something else.

title: Add nfc
body: Option - touch an NFC tag to silence the alarm.

title: Refactoring
body:
Model:
- Use calendars instead of time in millis to make things more clear and readable
- Move decision making from the Alarm class to a dedicated comparator
- Move Database interaction to a dedicated repository class
- Make Alarm an information expert. Alarm knows better what to do when it is changed.

title: Use light during pre-alarm
body:
according to http://habrahabr.ru/post/149159/
при свете разрушается гормон сна мелатонин, начинает вырабатываться гормон пробуждения кортизол. Умная лампа включается за полчаса до нужного времени. Но не сразу на полную мощность, а постепенно увеличивая яркость. Одновременно начинают петь птички и шуметь лес – все громче и громче. Плюс, в нужное время зазвучит мелодия.

I find this awesome.

title: When snoozed alarm fires, snooze notification remains
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: Snooze notification has to be removed

title: New interface for tablets
body:
It turns out that for tablets we need something else.
Currently I can come up with:
- Fullscreen interface with desktop background
- Fullscreen interface with analog clock widget
- Fullscreen interface with fragments (like Settings application)
- Dialog interface with buttons

Currently we are using "Dialog interface with buttons". Problem is that there is no access to settings and it does not look very nice. I really think full screen wil look better. What we can do is take a look at other alarms, like doubleTwist alarm.

title: Alarm dialog cannot be closed if alarm was deleted
label: [Label(name="bug")]

title: Add a logger
body: logger should be able to log everything to the logcat, file, or textview and should be responsible for switching channels on and off. And a way to catch runtime exceptions would be nice as well. This logger can be used to gather info from beta testers in the background (once a day send an email).

title: Add bottom action bar
body: Buttons go to sleep now and go to bed. On the top we can display an icon, settings icon and time to the next alarm. Or vice versa - buttons on top, status on bottom.

title: New alarm is added when rotating SetAlarmActivity
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: Alarm should be reverted on destroy or new activity should get its id.

title: Add one-shot alarms
body:
Add a checkbox into the SetAlarmActivity to make an Alarm a one-shot Alarm. Alarms added this way cannot be enabled or disabled, they can be only removed. They are removed automatically when they fire. This requires GUI, Alarm and DB changes. 

This should be configurable in Settings (or not?, please vote)

title: Add "Go to bed now" button in the main Activity
body:
This button should start a SetAlarmActivity. SetAlarmActivity should add a slider as a second way to set time and show how many hours there are to sleep. As an alternative (for future?), button can replaced with a "drawer handle" to slide in the layout. These are one-shot alarms.

This should be configurable in settings.

title: Highlight the next scheduled alarm in the list?
body: This should be configurable in settings

title: Add a notification to show next scheduled alarm
label: [Label(name="Next")]
body:
This should be configurable in settings.

Think about optional additional buttons: edit, skip occurence, etc.

title: Add a View in the main Activity, which shows the next Alarm
body: This has to be configurable in settings

label: [Label(name="bug")]

title: Snooze time can be 62 minutes, etc

body: Seems that it only affects logs, so low priority.

title: When alarm is snoozed there is no way to dismiss it
body: Add a notification to dismiss snoozed alarms.

title: Make action bar buttons with text
body: For this remove the application icon

title: Expired non-repeating alarms are not disabled on boot
label: [Label(name="bug")]

title: Add context menu triangles to the list
body: In the main list use context menu triangles instead of long-click

title: ListActivity notifyDataSetChanged
body: Use notifyDataSetChanged instead of clear() and set().

title: Reduce DB access
body: We don't have to update DB everytime something is changed. We have to get data from it on app start and flush it when app ends or major changes happen).

title: Snooze does not work
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: Snooze does not work yet, enabling snooze leads to the feedback loop of "Fired - Fire next immediately"
